canonical:
  title: 杏花
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 平生最是戀風光今日花前興欲狂願借漆園胡蝶夢遶枝攀蘂恣飛揚
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 杏花
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 平生最是戀風光。今日花前興欲狂。願借漆園胡蝶夢。遶枝攀蘂恣飛揚。
korean:
  title: 행화
  author: 최유청
  language: kor
  text: |-
    평생에 좋아하긴 풍광을 그리는 일
    오늘 꽃 앞에 흥이 미치겠고야
    원컨댄 칠원(漆園)의 나비꿈을 빌어서
    가지를 돌고 꽃술에 앉으며 마음대로 날고저
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0410&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 칠원(漆園) : '
    value: 장자(莊子)를 지칭한다. 일찍이 칠원(漆園) 땅의 관원으로 있었기 때문에 붙여진 이름이다.
english:
  title: Apricot Blossoms
  author: Choe Yu-cheong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    All my life I have cherished the beauty of nature's changing light.
    Today before these flowers, my spirit threatens to break free.
    I wish to borrow the butterfly dream of the man of Qi Garden,
    That I might circle the branches and dance upon the stamens,
    Flying wild and unrestrained.
  footnotes:
    - The 'man of Qi Garden' refers to Zhuangzi, who once served as an official in that region. The poet invokes Zhuangzi's famous parable of dreaming he was a butterfly, using it as a metaphor for transcendence and liberation through communion with nature.
